Description: Two joining fragments of large Attic black-glazed pottery open vase with handle root. Glazed save for part of reserved panel between handle roots. Incised inscription on inside.
Bibliographic references: Edgar 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis. B: The Inscribed and Painted Pottery (no. 95)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 703, no. 618)
Höckmann & Möller 2006 / The Hellenion at Naukratis: Questions and Observations (p.14 fig. 7,3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1707)
